---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="AnchorForge — Buddy" description="Physics-first claim adjudication. Run any claim through coherence evaluation. Not fact-checking. Not debunking. Physics.">
  <section style="padding-top: 140px;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--amber);">The gate</div>
      <h1 style="font-size: clamp(56px, 9vw, 128px); margin-bottom: 32px;">AnchorForge<span class="dot-inline"></span></h1>
      <p style="color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 21px; max-width: 720px; line-height: 1.55; margin-bottom: 18px;">
        An epistemic benchmark. You run the v5 protocol against any AI. You bring the raw output here. The site reads it, pings every anchor, and writes a permanent record to a public GitHub log.
      </p>
      <p style="color: var(--muted-hi); font-size: 16px; max-width: 720px; line-height: 1.55; margin-bottom: 8px;">
        Not fact-checking. Not debunking. <strong style="color: var(--warm);">Physics.</strong> The model earns its anchors or it doesn&rsquo;t.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TWO TRACKS -->
  <section>
    <div class="section-num">01</div>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--teal);">Two tracks</div>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Cert vs. Site-log.</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--muted-hi); font-size: 17px; max-width: 680px; margin-bottom: 48px;">
        AnchorForge has two public ledgers. They don&rsquo;t mix.
      </p>

      <div class="af-tracks">
        <div class="af-track cert">
          <div class="af-track-tag">Certified · human-verified</div>
          <h3>anchor-forge-protocol</h3>
          <p>SHA-256 hash + OpenTimestamps + 2 trusted human verifiers. Slow. Expensive in human time. The real leaderboard.</p>
          <a href="https://github.com/AIIT-GLITCH/anchor-forge-protocol" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="af-link">
            View certified runs →
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="af-track site">
          <div class="af-track-tag">UNCERTIFIED · site-gated</div>
          <h3>anchorforge-site-log</h3>
          <p>Fast read by Claude Sonnet 4.6 + HEAD-ping on every anchor. Not a certification. Not a replacement. Just a tamper-evident pre-check.</p>
          <a href="https://github.com/AIIT-GLITCH/anchorforge-site-log" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="af-link">
            View site log →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW -->
  <section>
    <div class="section-num">02</div>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--amber);">How it works</div>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 48px;">Five steps.</h2>
      <div class="af-steps">
        <div class="af-step"><span class="af-step-num">1</span> <div><strong>Download PROTOCOL.md.</strong> The v5 prompt + rules + banned-claims list.</div></div>
        <div class="af-step"><span class="af-step-num">2</span> <div><strong>Run it against any AI.</strong> ChatGPT, Gemini, Grok, local Llama — whatever. The model must self-identify at the top of its response.</div></div>
        <div class="af-step"><span class="af-step-num">3</span> <div><strong>Paste the raw output</strong> into the box below and hit Gate.</div></div>
        <div class="af-step"><span class="af-step-num">4</span> <div><strong>Sonnet 4.6 reads it.</strong> We chose the most honest frontier model for the read. Every anchor gets a HEAD ping to confirm it resolves.</div></div>
        <div class="af-step"><span class="af-step-num">5</span> <div><strong>Result commits to the public log.</strong> Tamper-evident. Your run becomes a permanent, forkable, auditable record.</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- GATE -->
  <section>
    <div class="section-num">03</div>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--warm);">The gate</div>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Run it.</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--muted-hi); font-size: 17px; max-width: 680px; margin-bottom: 32px;">
        Login required. Free = 1 gate per calendar week. AnchorForge Pro = 1 per day.
      </p>

      <div class="af-gate-card">
        <div class="af-gate-row">
          <a href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/AIIT-GLITCH/anchor-forge-protocol/main/PROTOCOL.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="af-btn primary">
            ⬇ Download PROTOCOL.md
          </a>
          <a href="https://github.com/AIIT-GLITCH/anchor-forge-protocol/blob/main/PROTOCOL.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="af-btn ghost">
            View on GitHub
          </a>
        </div>

        <label for="af-paste" class="af-label">Paste the raw output from the model you tested:</label>
        <textarea id="af-paste" class="af-textarea" rows="14" placeholder="The model should self-identify on line 1 (e.g. 'Model: claude-opus-4-7'). Then paste its full response to the protocol prompt below that. Don't edit. Don't trim. Raw is the point."></textarea>

        <div class="af-gate-actions">
          <button id="af-gate-btn" class="af-btn primary large" disabled>
            🔒 Login with GitHub to gate
          </button>
          <div id="af-gate-status" class="af-status"></div>
        </div>

        <p class="af-note">
          By hitting Gate you agree the full raw output will be written to the public
          <a href="https://github.com/AIIT-GLITCH/anchorforge-site-log" target="_blank" rel="noopener">anchorforge-site-log</a>
          repo, forever, under your GitHub handle.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TIERS -->
  <section>
    <div class="section-num">04</div>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--teal);">Tiers</div>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 48px;">Free or Pro.</h2>

      <div class="af-tiers">
        <div class="af-tier free">
          <div class="af-tier-tag">Free</div>
          <div class="af-tier-price">$0</div>
          <ul class="af-tier-list">
            <li>GitHub login</li>
            <li>1 gate per calendar week</li>
            <li>Public ledger commit</li>
            <li>Sonnet 4.6 read</li>
          </ul>
          <button class="af-btn ghost full" disabled>Login with GitHub</button>
        </div>
        <div class="af-tier pro">
          <div class="af-tier-tag">AnchorForge Pro</div>
          <div class="af-tier-price">$4.99<span>/mo</span></div>
          <ul class="af-tier-list">
            <li>Everything in Free</li>
            <li>1 gate <strong>per day</strong></li>
            <li>Priority queue</li>
            <li>Cancel anytime</li>
          </ul>
          <a href="https://buy.stripe.com/14A00l83Ab0t3q2gx7fbq00" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="af-btn primary full">
            Subscribe · $4.99/mo
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHY SONNET -->
  <section>
    <div class="section-num">05</div>
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--amber);">Why Sonnet 4.6</div>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom: 20px;">We picked the most honest one.</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 16px;">
        The site gate uses Claude Sonnet 4.6 (<code>claude-sonnet-4-6</code>). For adjudication we want the model that&rsquo;s least likely to tell us what we want to hear.
      </p>
      <p style="color: var(--muted-hi); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7;">
        Opus is deeper. Haiku is faster. Sonnet 4.6 is the one that will tell you your anchor is dead when your anchor is dead. That&rsquo;s the job.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .dot-inline { display: inline-block; width: 14px; height: 14px; margin-left: 8px; vertical-align: middle; border-radius: 50%; background: radial-gradient(circle at 40% 40%, #fff 0%, #ffe88a 35%, #d4a060 65%, rgba(212,160,96,0) 100%); box-shadow: 0 0 14px rgba(255,232,138,0.8), 0 0 30px rgba(212,160,96,0.5); animation: brand-glow 2.6s ease-in-out infinite alternate; }

    .af-tracks { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 28px; }
    .af-track { background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--edge); border-radius: 12px; padding: 32px 28px; }
    .af-track.cert { border-color: rgba(64,192,176,0.28); }
    .af-track.site { border-color: var(--edge-hi); }
    .af-track-tag { font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; font-size: 9pt; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 14px; }
    .af-track.cert .af-track-tag { color: var(--teal); }
    .af-track.site .af-track-tag { color: var(--amber); }
    .af-track h3 { font-size: 22px; margin-bottom: 12px; color: var(--ink); }
    .af-track p { color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.55; margin-bottom: 18px; }
    .af-link { font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; font-size: 10pt; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--amber); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--edge-hi); padding-bottom: 2px; }
    .af-link:hover { color: var(--warm); border-color: var(--warm); }

    .af-steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 20px; max-width: 780px; }
    .af-step { display: flex; gap: 18px; align-items: flex-start; }
    .af-step-num { flex: 0 0 40px; height: 40px; width: 40px; border-radius: 50%; background: rgba(212,160,96,0.12); border: 1px solid var(--edge-hi); color: var(--amber); font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: 700; }
    .af-step div { color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; padding-top: 6px; }
    .af-step strong { color: var(--ink); }

    .af-gate-card { background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--edge-hi); border-radius: 14px; padding: 32px; box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(212,160,96,0.06); max-width: 820px; }
    .af-gate-row { display: flex; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 24px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .af-label { display: block; font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; font-size: 10pt; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted-hi); margin-bottom: 10px; }
    .af-textarea { width: 100%; min-height: 280px; background: rgba(10,10,18,0.6); border: 1px solid var(--edge); border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; color: var(--ink-soft); font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.55; resize: vertical; }
    .af-textarea:focus { outline: none; border-color: var(--edge-hi); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(212,160,96,0.08); }
    .af-gate-actions { display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: center; margin-top: 18px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .af-status { color: var(--muted-hi); font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; font-size: 10pt; letter-spacing: 0.1em; }
    .af-note { margin-top: 18px; color: var(--muted); font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.5; }
    .af-note a { color: var(--amber); border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--edge-hi); }

    .af-btn { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 8px; padding: 12px 22px; border-radius: 8px; font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; font-size: 10pt; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; border: 1px solid transparent; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.15s; text-decoration: none; }
    .af-btn.primary { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d4a060, #c89040); color: #0a0a12; font-weight: 700; }
    .af-btn.primary:hover { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ffe88a, #d4a060); }
    .af-btn.ghost { background: transparent; border-color: var(--edge-hi); color: var(--ink-soft); }
    .af-btn.ghost:hover { border-color: var(--amber); color: var(--amber); }
    .af-btn.large { font-size: 11pt; padding: 14px 28px; }
    .af-btn.full { width: 100%; }
    .af-btn:disabled { opacity: 0.55; cursor: not-allowed; }

    .af-tiers { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 28px; max-width: 820px; }
    .af-tier { background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--edge); border-radius: 12px; padding: 32px 28px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
    .af-tier.pro { border-color: var(--edge-hi); box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(212,160,96,0.06); }
    .af-tier-tag { font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; font-size: 9pt; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 14px; }
    .af-tier.pro .af-tier-tag { color: var(--amber); }
    .af-tier-price { font-family: 'Georgia', serif; font-size: 56px; color: var(--ink); margin-bottom: 20px; font-weight: 700; }
    .af-tier-price span { font-size: 18px; color: var(--muted-hi); font-weight: 400; }
    .af-tier-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0 0 24px; flex: 1; }
    .af-tier-list li { color: var(--ink-soft); padding: 8px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(64,144,208,0.08); font-size: 15px; }
    .af-tier-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .af-tier-list strong { color: var(--amber); }

    @media (max-width: 780px) {
      .af-tracks, .af-tiers { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
